==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dyslexia
<hw>dys*lex"i*a</hw> <pr>(d⟦icr⟧s*l⟦ecr⟧ks"⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of various reading disorders caused by a damaged
or congenitally faulty structure within the central nervous system, and
causing an impairment of the ability to interpret spatial relationships
or to integrate auditory and visual information. A common example is
when letter sequences are interpreted as inverted in order, as in
<b><i>bat/tab</i></b>.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dyslexic</ent>⟦br⟧
